String Class:

		String is most widely used class in Java. It helps us store and manipulate text based data.
		
Why we should learn about String class and its methods?

		String class has a lot of methods that can help us manipulate text based data.
		That way we don't need to write any logic, we can simply create the object of the String class and can use method from that class.
		
Syntax for String class:

		String str=new String("I can't sleep if I don't solve repls");
								OR
		String str2="I can't sleep if I don't solve repls";
		
		str2.length();